{
  "stem": "93.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This was a little bit difficult for me to accept at the time, because I was 25 years old, recently graduated, only three months or four months before from the Military Academy.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I realized that there was something here of importance.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I took this soldier to my Division G2.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The assistant division G2 was himself Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I turned this soldier over to him, so that at least as early as December of 1942, somebody in the official chain knew of the existence of-- of concentration camps, at least within the military chain of command.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, we, as a division, went to Europe in June of 1945.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we landed in England sometime in mid June, late June.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The date is not really important.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we went to Europe in early August and landed on Omaha Beach.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, I think maybe I should just give you a brief description of what we did.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were in the-- in the great breakthrough and the pincer movement at Avranches, which destroyed the German armies that had been defending the-- the beaches.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The result of that pincer movement was a mass killing, most of which occurred around Avranches.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We proceeded from there across France in what was really a very rapid movement until we got to the Meuse River.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "At the Meuse River, we encountered the Germans very, very briefly, but they had been unable to establish a defense.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we broke across the Meuse River very, very rapidly and went to the Moselle River, where we arrived perhaps the 6th of September, 7th of September, something of that sort, 1944.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In the initial attempt to cross that river, the division was ordered to execute what was known as a hasty crossing.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
